				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I like this idea.
<br />

<br />
As for when the aggro problem rears its ugly head; with a paladin tank I cannot drop more than half mana on Ikatiar without being summoned.
<br />

<br />
With a warrior tank I cannot drop more than 40% on longer fights, unless the duration is prolonged by an AE and the possibility of hiding from it (ST Ancients). 
<br />

<br />
I do not want concussion, but I want a way to stop being a laughable raid damage dealer. To those who say we are not, I must respond that I am perceived that way. LDoN's pet protection line will help my damage output nicely, but it will likely not be enough to make me a respected damage dealer.
<br />

<br />
Again, I do not want to step on anyone's toes -- I do not play a wizard, or rogue, or ranger, and so my knowledge of their viewpoint is limited to what I read and discuss. However, I believe that with cooperation we can assist each other in these issues while maintaining balance.
<br />

<br />
