			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I suggested this idea in another thread, andI don't like the idea of it rooting you in place. My original suggestion was for it to be a spell, so it would be more readily available to all over a dropped item, but none the less to prevent abuse for aggro kiting purposes just make the cast time on it 8 seconds.
<br />

<br />
8 seconds is long enough that if your aggro kiting the mob will reach you to kill you, if you have to stop to recast it. If your in a raid, and it pops, and your saved, waiting 8 seconds or a bit more is prudent, to make sure you drop a bit more off the hate list. The entire idea is to have the magician drop lower on the hate list so they can resume nuking mobs. 
<br />

<br />
Rooting you in place is very bad because you may have to drop the shield to move if the mob is pushed out of range, and recast it, lowering our DPS even more than it should be, waiting another 8-10 seconds to recast it. 
<br />

<br />
The first discussion I said let it be a 300 mana spell, no reagant, with a 60-90 minute duration. If used you recast it, if it goes off, but wipes all your hate or some high number. The mana cost and cast times make it not for abuse, but to allow us to make a contribuition on the end game.
<br />

<br />
So how does a spell as porposed, AND a dropped item with the same effect, to save the mana cost. So all mages would have access to it, and those in the area's the item may drop get a free version of it, to help them nuke more in the end game of whatever expansion your on. 
<br />

<br />
Also if a dropped item make it like the elemental legs for the wizards, off any of the gods in the elemental planes, and in PoTime, just a different item in Time, so those that already are in Time will have access to it also, without farming older content. Make it a different slot, and with 2 effects a Magician would want.
<br />

<br />
Calebe</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
